results.name: Smallest m>0 such that (2n-1)2^m+1 is prime, or -1 if no such value exists.
comment: There exist odd integers 2k-1 such that (2k-1)2^n+1 is always composite.
reference: Ribenboim, P. The New Book of Prime Number Records. New York: Springer-Verlag, pp. 357-359, 1996.
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..1000
xref: Cf. A046067 (except for initial term a(1) identical to this sequence), A046068, A046069, A046070.
results.author: _Eric W. Weisstein_
